======================================================

          Ermlab Software recruitment task: 

   1) Feedback visualization using chart (distinguish 
by type: positive, neutral, negative),

   2) Histogram for reviews lengths (e.g. 0-20, 20-40
should be readable), 

  3) Filter positive and negative feedbacks which are 
min. 100 characters long, 

  4) Find correlation between length of text and 
feedback type.

  5) Find and visualize interesting relation between 
features of given dataset. 


  Preconditions:
    Python > 3.6 
    Hosted on GitHub
    README included
    Pandas library used

======================================================

          Installation and usage: 

   1. Clone repository, 
   2. To use analyse module for sentiment dataset 
      invoke analyse.py with two required arguments. 

      python3 analyse.py [-s | -d] <dataset_path>
        
        -s    Saves charts to repository directory. 
        -d    Displays charts on the fly.

      Example: 
        python3 analyse.py -s /home/user/dataset.csv

   3. Other results related to the task, will be printed
   at the terminal window.

